
[1]pun

   PUN, n. An expression in which a word has at once different meanings;
   an expression in which two different applications of a word present an
   odd or ludicrous idea; a kind of quibble or equivocation; a low species
   of wit. Thus a man who had a tall wife named Experience, observed that
   he had, by long experience, proved the blessings of a married life.

   A pun can be no more engraven,than it can be translated.

   PUN, v.i. To quibble; to use the same word at once in different senses.

                       PUN, v.t. To persuade by a pun.
